    "created_at": "2017-10-30T11:11:13Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-10-30T11:11:13Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "It depends on a few factors. If the miner's fee is X, anything below X will be discarded. As such, even if you lower the price, the transaction was already thrown out by the miner, so the only way to process it, is if the miner gets the transaction back somehow. In a large network, this can happen since nodes come and go and shuffle transactions between each other. In a small private network where connections are stabe, it might happen that it's never rebroadcast. If you restart your node though it should push it out again.",
